{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "15", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "13", "M": "05", "S": "50"}}, "news": [{"title": "Empty skyscrapers: China's property slump still throttling growth", "para": "The world's tallest unoccupied skyscraper was meant to boast a rooftop pool and a luxury hotel after completion, but instead it has stood deserted in the Chinese port city of Tianjin for years. The 595.5-metre (1,954-foot) skyscraper is emblematic of the years-long crisis that has left Chinese cities dotted with abandoned high-rises and residential towers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/chinas-property-slump-leaves-skyscrapers-empty-a-sign-of-economic-crisis/132412433?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-351774/132412433.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "international"}, {"title": "Kalyan-Dombivli civic body fines Titwala township for failing to process waste", "para": "The Kalyan-Dombivli Municipal Corporation imposed a one lakh rupee penalty on Regency Sarvam township. This action followed repeated complaints about non-functional waste processing facilities within the complex. Civic officials found the in-house waste processing plant was not operational during an inspection. The township had previously received notices to restore its waste processing system. Strict action will continue against establishments failing to comply with waste management norms.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/kalyan-dombivli-municipal-corporation-fines-titwala-township-for-waste-mismanagement/132410487?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-414759/132410487.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Karnataka government unveils new apartment bill to safeguard property owners' interests", "para": "Karnataka unveiled a new bill to replace outdated apartment ownership laws. This legislation aims to protect owners' rights and streamline complex management. It will apply to projects with over eight units and establish a competent authority. The bill mandates structural checks and offers dispute resolution mechanisms. Redevelopment will require owner consent and fair compensation for all parties.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/karnataka-government-unveils-new-apartment-bill-to-safeguard-property-owners-interests/132411632?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-161357/132411632.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}